parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden failure of the brake pedal can lead to loss of control, accidents, and injuries, especially in situations where the vehicle is traveling at high speeds or navigating slippery roads.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal travels to the floor
the brake pedal fades or loses pressure
the vehicle slides or rolls away when the brake pedal is applied
the anti-lock brake system (ABS) fails to engage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the upper ball joint can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially lead to serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The upper ball joint falls off while driving
the vehicle pulls to one side
uneven tire wear
loose or noisy steering
vibrations in the steering wheel or seat.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The electrical short circuit in the tail light can cause the lights to malfunction or fail, reducing visibility and increasing the risk of accidents, especially at night or in low-light conditions.
symptoms: The tail lights do not function
the tail lights flicker or dim
the tail lights are intermittent
the tail lights are completely dark
the vehicle's electrical system is affected.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The lock-up of the front seat belt retractor can cause the seat belt to malfunction, potentially leading to injury or fatality in the event of an accident. This issue can also cause inconvenience and discomfort to the occupants.
symptoms: The front seat belt retractor locks up
the seat belt fails to retract
the seat belt is stuck
the seat belt cannot be pulled out
the seat belt is difficult to use.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A loose steering wheel nut can cause the steering wheel to become detached from the steering column, leading to a loss of vehicle control, which can increase the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The steering wheel feels loose or wobbly
the steering wheel nut requires frequent tightening
the steering wheel is difficult to turn
the vehicle pulls to one side while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Improper torque of the steering wheel nut can cause the steering wheel to become loose or detached, leading to a loss of vehicle control, which can increase the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The steering wheel feels loose or wobbly
the steering wheel nut requires frequent tightening
the steering wheel is difficult to turn
the vehicle pulls to one side while driving.
